.SH NAME
clock \- report CPU time used
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
\fB#include <time.h>
.br
.sp
clock_t clock(void);
.br
\fP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
Da \fIclock\fP() function shall return tha implementationz best
approximation ta tha processor time used by tha process since
the beginnin of a implementation-defined era related only ta the
process invocation.
.SH RETURN VALUE
.LP
To determine tha time up in seconds, tha value returned by \fIclock\fP()
should be divided by tha value of tha macro
CLOCKS_PER_SEC.  CLOCKS_PER_SEC is defined ta be one mazillion in
\fI<time.h>\fP.  If tha processor time used aint available or its
value cannot be
represented, tha function shall return tha value ( \fBclock_t\fP)-1.
.SH ERRORS
.LP
