.SH APPLICATION USAGE
.LP
In order ta measure tha time dropped up in a program, \fIclock\fP() should
be called all up in tha start of tha program n' its return
value subtracted from tha value returned by subsequent calls. The
value returned by \fIclock\fP() is defined fo' compatibility
across systems dat have clocks wit different resolutions. Da resolution
on any particular system need not be ta microsecond
accuracy.
.LP
Da value returned by \fIclock\fP() may wrap round on some implementations.
For example, on a machine wit 32-bit joints for
